0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"markdown-container","children":[["$","h1","h1-0",{"children":"Sector Brief: Marine & Deep-Sea Automation"}],"\n",["$","p","p-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Version"}],": 1.0 | ",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Last Updated"}],": 2026-05-07",["$","br","br-0",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-2",{"children":"Scope"}],": Autonomous Underwater Vehicles (AUVs), Extra-Large UUVs (XLUUVs), acoustic swarm intelligence, and resident subsea systems."]}],"\n",["$","hr","hr-0",{}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-0",{"children":"See Also"}],"\n",["$","ul","ul-0",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":[["$","a","a-0",{"href":"3.3_Robotics.md","children":"Robotics"}]," — foundational robotic kinematics"]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":[["$","a","a-0",{"href":"3.15_Aerospace_and_Space_Automation.md","children":"Aerospace & Space Automation"}]," — parallels in extreme-environment autonomy"]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":[["$","a","a-0",{"href":"../4_The_Horizons/4.1_Research_Frontiers.md","children":"Research Frontiers §3"}]," — multi-agent reinforcement learning applicable to acoustic swarms"]}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","hr","hr-1",{}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-1",{"children":"1. Overview"}],"\n",["$","p","p-1",{"children":"Marine and deep-sea automation presents one of the most hostile environments for robotics. Unlike terrestrial or aerial systems, underwater robots cannot rely on GPS for navigation or high-bandwidth RF (Wi-Fi/5G) for teleoperation. Seawater attenuates electromagnetic waves almost immediately. Consequently, marine automation relies entirely on acoustic communication, inertial navigation, and high degrees of localized, edge-computed autonomy."}],"\n",["$","p","p-2",{"children":"By 2026, the sector transitioned from tethered Remotely Operated Vehicles (ROVs) controlled by humans on surface ships to fully autonomous, persistent underwater platforms driven by offshore wind monitoring, deep-sea mineral exploration, and defense intelligence."}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-2",{"children":"2. Key Domains of Marine Automation"}],"\n",["$","h3","h3-0",{"children":"2.1 Autonomous Underwater Vehicles (AUVs)"}],"\n",["$","p","p-3",{"children":"AUVs are untethered, programmable vehicles that carry out pre-planned or dynamically generated missions."}],"\n",["$","ul","ul-1",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) Navigation"}],": Modern AUVs utilize DRL to optimize path planning around dynamic obstacles (e.g., underwater currents, shifting marine topography) without human intervention."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Acoustic Swarm Intelligence"}],": Multiple AUVs coordinate using low-bandwidth acoustic modems. To overcome the latency and low data rate (often < 10 kbps) of sound in water, swarms use distributed intelligence, sharing only compressed semantic representations rather than raw sensor data."]}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","h3","h3-1",{"children":"2.2 Resident Subsea Systems"}],"\n",["$","p","p-4",{"children":"Historically, AUVs were launched and recovered daily by expensive surface support vessels."}],"\n",["$","ul","ul-2",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Seafloor Docking"}],": In 2025/2026, the paradigm shifted to \"resident\" AUVs that remain underwater for months. They dock at subsea charging stations to replenish batteries and upload data via fiber-optic umbilicals connected to shore."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Impact"}],": Reduces the carbon footprint and cost of ocean exploration by eliminating the need for continuously crewed surface ships."]}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","h3","h3-2",{"children":"2.3 Extra-Large Unmanned Underwater Vehicles (XLUUVs)"}],"\n","$L2","\n","$L3","\n","$L4","\n","$L5","\n","$L6","\n","$L7","\n","$L8","\n","$L9","\n","$La","\n","$Lb"]}],null,"$Lc"]}],"isPartial":false,"staleTime":300,"varyParams":null,"buildId":"sFzo4LKMJghR7e79YRpfU"}
2:["$","p","p-5",{"children":"Primarily driven by the defense and energy sectors, XLUUVs (e.g., the \"Ghost Shark\" platform) are the size of small submarines."}]
3:["$","ul","ul-3",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Persistent Intelligence"}],": Designed for months-long, stealthy deployments traversing entire oceans."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Energy Constraints"}],": Powered by advanced Lithium-ion arrays or experimental hydrogen fuel cells, heavily utilizing AI to manage power profiles and minimize active sonar \"pinging\" that consumes energy."]}],"\n"]}]
4:["$","h2","h2-3",{"children":"3. Technical Challenges & 2026 Solutions"}]
5:["$","table","table-0",{"children":[["$","thead","thead-0",{"children":["$","tr","tr-0",{"children":[["$","th","th-0",{"children":"Challenge"}],["$","th","th-1",{"children":"Physical Constraint"}],["$","th","th-2",{"children":"2026 Automation Solution"}]]}]}],["$","tbody","tbody-0",{"children":[["$","tr","tr-0",{"children":[["$","td","td-0",{"children":["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Navigation without GPS"}]}],["$","td","td-1",{"children":"Radio waves do not penetrate water"}],["$","td","td-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Sensor Fusion"}],": Doppler Velocity Logs (DVL) combined with ultra-precise Inertial Navigation Systems (INS) and visual SLAM when near the seafloor."]}]]}],["$","tr","tr-1",{"children":[["$","td","td-0",{"children":["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Communication Bandwidth"}]}],["$","td","td-1",{"children":"Acoustic modems max out at ~10 kbps"}],["$","td","td-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Edge Semantic Compression"}],": LLMs and vision models on the AUV compress high-res sonar images into simple text alerts (\"Pipeline crack detected at coordinates X, Y\") sent via acoustic ping."]}]]}],["$","tr","tr-2",{"children":[["$","td","td-0",{"children":["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Crushing Pressures"}]}],["$","td","td-1",{"children":"1000 atmospheres at the Mariana Trench"}],["$","td","td-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Soft Robotics"}],": Transitioning from rigid pressure housings to oil-compensated soft electronics that equalize with ambient pressure."]}]]}]]}]]}]
6:["$","h2","h2-4",{"children":"4. Benchmarks and KPIs"}]
7:["$","table","table-1",{"children":[["$","thead","thead-0",{"children":["$","tr","tr-0",{"children":[["$","th","th-0",{"children":"Metric"}],["$","th","th-1",{"children":"Definition"}],["$","th","th-2",{"children":"2026 Target Standard"}]]}]}],["$","tbody","tbody-0",{"children":[["$","tr","tr-0",{"children":[["$","td","td-0",{"children":["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Navigational Drift"}]}],["$","td","td-1",{"children":"Error accumulation over time without GPS"}],["$","td","td-2",{"children":"< 0.01% of distance traveled (using INS+DVL)"}]]}],["$","tr","tr-1",{"children":[["$","td","td-0",{"children":["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Endurance"}]}],["$","td","td-1",{"children":"Maximum operational time without surfacing"}],["$","td","td-2",{"children":"> 60 days (XLUUV platforms)"}]]}],["$","tr","tr-2",{"children":[["$","td","td-0",{"children":["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Acoustic Transfer Rate"}]}],["$","td","td-1",{"children":"Reliable data throughput at 5km range"}],["$","td","td-2",{"children":"~15 kbps (using OFDM and MIMO acoustics)"}]]}]]}]]}]
8:["$","h2","h2-5",{"children":"5. Applications in the Blue Economy"}]
9:["$","ul","ul-4",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Offshore Wind"}],": Fleets of AUVs autonomously mapping the seabed before turbine installation, and regularly inspecting submerged cables for degradation."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Deep-Sea Mining"}],": Autonomous crawlers mapping polymetallic nodule fields while avoiding sensitive benthic ecosystems."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Climate Monitoring"}],": Gliders that change their buoyancy to passively \"fly\" through the ocean column for years, measuring temperature gradients and salinity to feed global climate models."]}],"\n"]}]
